{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> θάνᾰτος</b> [θᾰ], ὁ, <br /> (θνῄσκω) <b>death</b>, whether natural or violent, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus, etc.\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; τῶν ὑπαλευάμενος θάνατον <b>the death threatened</b> by them, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 15.275; ὣς θάνον οἰκτίστῳ θανάτῳ 11.412 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; θάνατόνδε <b>to death</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 16.693, 22.297 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; θανάτου τέλος, μοῖρα, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 906 (Lyric poetry), “Pers.” 917 (_anapaest meter_), etc.\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; θανάτου πέρι καὶ ζωᾶς for life and <b>death</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “N.” 9.29; θ. ἢ βίον φέρει 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 802; θάνατος μὲν τάδ᾽ ἀκούειν [prev. author] “OC” 529; θανάτῳ ἴσον πάθος [prev. author] “Aj.” 215; ἐν ἀγχόναις θάνατον λαβεῖν 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Helena” 201 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πόλεώς ἐστι θ., ἀνάστατον γενέσθαι it is its <b>death</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Lycurgus Orator 61 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; γῆρας ζῶν θ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Secundus Gnomologus “Sententiae - FPG” 12 \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]; θάνατον ἀποθνῄσκειν, τελευτᾶν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Crassus” 25, 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 4.76. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> in Law, <b>death-penalty</b>, θάνατον καταγνῶναί τινος to pass <b>sentence of death</b> on one, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.81 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; θανάτου δίκῃ κρίνεσθαι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. work] 57; θανάτου κρίνειν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.2.14, 2nd c.BC: Polybius Historicus 6.14.6; περὶ θανάτου διώκειν 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 7.3.6 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πρὸς τοὺς ἐχθροὺς.. ἀγωνίσασθαι περὶ θ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 4.47 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; θ. τῆς ζημίας ἐπικειμένης the penalty is <b>death</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 8.50 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; elliptically, παιδίον κεκος μημένον τὴν ἐπὶ θανάτῳ (i.e. στολήν) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.109; τὴν ἐπὶ θ. προσαγαγεῖν τινα 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “Alex.” 44 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; but δῆσαί τινα τὴν ἐπὶ θανάτῳ (i.e. δέσιν) [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.119 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὴν ἐπὶ θανάτῳ ἔξοδον ποιεῖσθαι to go to <b>execution</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 7.223; ἐπὶ θάνατον ἄγεσθαι [prev. author] 3.14 \">Refs</a>]; τοῖς Ἀθηναίοις ἐπιτρέψαι περὶ σφῶν αὐτῶν πλὴν θανάτου for any penalty short of <b>death</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 4.54; εὐθύνας εἶναι πλὴν φυγῆς καὶ θανάτου καὶ ἀτιμίας “IG” 12.39.73 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; εἰργόμενον θανάτου καὶ τοῦ ἀνάπηρον ποιῆσαι short <b>of death</b> or maiming, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 1.183. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <i>plural</i>, θάνατοι <b>kinds of death</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 12.341 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>the deaths</b> of several persons, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1200, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Heraclidae” 628 (both Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <i>poetry</i>, of one person, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 53, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 496, “El.” 206 (all Lyric poetry); οὐχ ἑνός, οὐδὲ δυοῖν ἄξια θανάτοιν 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 908e; πολλῶν θ., οὐχ ἑνὸς ἄξιος 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 21.21, compare 19.16, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Plutus” 483, 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis 4.24; δεύτερος θ. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>*<i>apocalyptic</i></b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2.11, compare 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.942f\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]; especially of <b>violent death</b>, θ. αὐθένται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 1572 (Lyric poetry), compare “Th.” 879 (Lyric poetry); εἰς θανάτους ἰέναι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 399b. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> as <i>proper name</i>, Θάνατος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Death”, Ὕπνῳ.. κασιγνήτῳ Θανάτοιο 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.231, compare 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 854, “Ph.” 797, etc.; μόνος θεῶν γὰρ Θ. οὐ δώρων ἐρᾷ 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Fragmenta - American Journal of Philology” 161 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ὃν [ἰὸν] τέκετο Θ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 834; character in 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus Alcaeus \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>corpse</b>, θ. ἀτύμβευτος [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Anthologia Graeca” 9.439 (1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Crinagoras Epigrammaticus). \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G2288","accentedUnicode":"θάνατος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0110","matchingForm":"ἀθανασία","stepTransliteration":"athanasia","gloss":"immortality","_zh_tw_Gloss":"不死","_es_Gloss":"inmortalidad","_zh_Gloss":"不死"},{"strongNumber":"G2286","matchingForm":"θανάσιμος","stepTransliteration":"thanasimos","gloss":"deadly","_zh_tw_Gloss":"致死毒物","_es_Gloss":"mortal","_zh_Gloss":"致死毒物"},{"strongNumber":"G2289","matchingForm":"θανατόω","stepTransliteration":"thanatoō","gloss":"to kill","_zh_tw_Gloss":"治死","_es_Gloss":"matar","_zh_Gloss":"治死"},{"strongNumber":"G2348","matchingForm":"θνῄσκω","stepTransliteration":"thnēskō","gloss":"to die/be dead","_zh_tw_Gloss":"死","_es_Gloss":"morir/estar muerto","_zh_Gloss":"死"}],"shortDef":"death","mediumDef":"<b>death, the extinction of life,</b> whether naturally, <ref='Luk.2.26'>Lk. 2:26</ref>; <ref='Mrk.9.1'>Mk. 9:1</ref>; or violently, <ref='Mat.10.21; 15:4'>Mt. 10:21; 15:4</ref>; <b>imminent danger of death,</b> <ref='2Co.4.11, 12; 11.23'>2Cor. 4:11, 12; 11:23</ref>; in NT spiritual <b>death,</b> as opposed to <greek>ζωή</greek> in its spiritual sense, in respect of a forfeiture of salvation, <ref='Jhn.8.51'>Jn. 8:51</ref>; <ref='Rom.6.16'>Rom. 6:16</ref>","stepGloss":"death","stepTransliteration":"thanatos","count":120,"_es_Definition":"muerte","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 死亡<br> 1a) 自然的死亡<br> 1b) 作為懲罰的死亡<br>  1a1) 世俗法庭宣判的死亡<br>  1b1) 基督之死<br>2) 離開神的死亡<br> 2a) 屬靈上的死<br> 2b) 永恆之死<br>3) (特殊的死亡方式) 致命的疾病, 瘟疫 (啟 2:33, 6:8, 18:8)","_zh_Definition":"1) 死亡<br> 1a) 自然的死亡<br> 1b) 作为惩罚的死亡<br> 1a1) 世俗法庭宣判的死亡<br> 1b1) 基督之死<br>2) 离开神的死亡<br > 2a) 属灵上的死<br> 2b) 永恒之死<br>3) (特殊的死亡方式) 致命的疾病, 瘟疫(启2:33, 6:8, 18:8)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"cái chết; sự chết; tử thần","_zh_tw_Gloss":"死","_es_Gloss":"muerte","_zh_Gloss":"死"}]}